President Obama spoke with President Preval of Haiti for about thirty minutes, expressing his condolences for the loss and suffering in Haiti. He pledged full support from the American people for both the immediate recovery and long-term rebuilding efforts. President Preval thanked the American people for their friendship and expressed gratitude for the support from America and other countries. Both presidents emphasized the importance of coordinating assistance efforts among various parties, including the Haitian government, the United Nations, the United States, and international partners and aid organizations. President Obama reiterated his commitment to supporting Haiti through his team on the ground. President Preval closed by thanking the American people on behalf of the Haitian people.